					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Let's clear one thing up: oam_stress.nes is NOT a test to test whether your emulator is accurate when compared to the real hardware. &quot;PASS&quot; doesn't mean that your emulator matches the real hardware, it means that the OAM reading works (whereas on the real NTSC PPU hardware, OAM reading does NOT work consistently).<br /><br />The &quot;test&quot; originates from here: <!-- l --><a class="postlink-local" href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=62044#p62044">viewtopic.php?p=62044#p62044</a><!-- l --></div>

					
